OBJECTIVE: To estimate the cost-effectiveness of universal group B streptococci 
(GBS) screening in women with a singleton pregnancy planning a repeat cesarean 
delivery.
METHODS: We conducted a decision analysis from a health care perspective to 
compare the cost-effectiveness of GBS screening for women planning a repeat 
cesarean delivery. With universal screening, all GBS-positive women who labored 
before a scheduled cesarean delivery received antibiotic prophylaxis. With no 
screening, women who presented in labor received antibiotics based on risk-based 
